Alright, we were able to get them going via remote support.

Here’s what I discovered/did:

  1. Observed user did not statically assign 192.168.69.x/24 to an ethernet adapter
  2. Assigned 192.168.69.2/24 to an ethernet adapter
  3. Observed multiple attempted firmware updates, but, used the wrong image
  4. After clearing out the failed attempts (can be done via a restart), reattempted 1.2.2 FW upgrade on their “field side” radio
  5. Was successful, configured their “field side” radio as a “Team Access Point”
  6. Had the remote user move the ethernet cable to their robot
  7. Performed the 1.2.2 FW upgrade on the “robot” radio
  8. Was successful, configured their “robot” radio with the same team number and password configured on the “field side” radio
  9. Observed the radio link come up and was able to reach the “field side” wirelessly
  10. Had remote user power cycle robot
  11. Observed that we still didn’t have robot connectivity on the driver station
  12. Remote user began troubleshooting and discovered that the ethernet cable to the roboRIO was unplugged and reseated it
  13. Observed that we now had full connectivity on the driver station through the “field side” radio configured as a “Team Access Point” to the robot
